ic patterns will be in place as Letcher is temporarily reopened June 29 for Summer Transition Program registration and July 2 5 for the balloon rally and Independence Day activities  A pedestrian detour is in place via Old Barracks through Daniels Courtyard and behind Shell Hall  while vehicles are being routed past the front of barracks and around the Parade Ground  Signage and barrier ropes are in place along the routes  Excavation in Memorial Garden is visible as crews are digging down 15 feet to the foundation of Cocke Hall to install waterproofing  Memorial Garden is closed while access to Memorial Wall remains open to visitors from Jackson Memorial Hall  On the other side of the Parade Ground  sidewalk work in front of Smith Hall will continue through the weekend  The rear entrance of Smith Hall should be used as construction continues  and the sidewalk between Smith and Moody halls remains accessible to pedestrians   VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 